Search to manually set your location
Apps can request a particular accuracy level. This is used to determine whether GPS/Wi-Fi are required.
The dialog can combine the access control request with the request to turn on devices.
Depending on the requested accuracy level, GPS and Wi-Fi might be needed. If they're off, switches are presented.
If a location is set from the search box, other controls go insensitive and switch to off.
